#Text=Browse Internet Websites Without Your Parents Knowing
#Text=Do you want to look at a website but do n't want your parents to know ?
#Text=This article will help you .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Incognito Browser Method
#Text=Find a website your parents will allow you to use .
#Text=Visit that website and keep the page open .
#Text=Find the website you want to use and open it up in a new window or tab .
#Text=Make sure to watch and listen for parents or anybody else that may tell on you .
#Text=If someone comes , quickly switch windows or tabs to the other website .
#Text=In Windows , you can quickly close the tab or window by pressing + .
#Text=In Linux , you can switch workspaces quickly using the mouse wheel .
#Text=Open your System Settings and click on Windows Manager Tweaks .
#Text=Then select Workspaces tab and check the Use the mouse wheel on the desktop to switch workspaces .
#Text=Clear your history .
#Text=When you 're finished , delete all the history on your computer that leads to any websites your parents do n't want you on .
#Text=In Firefox , there is actually an option you can select which will automatically clear your browsing history when you exit the browser .
#Text=This article will guide you in setting that up .
#Text=Using incognito mode !
#Text=This is a special window in the browser which , when used , does not record any internet data , history , or cache .
#Text=Most popular browser have such an option .
#Text=In Internet Explorer , you can press ++ to enter Private browsing .
#Text=To exit incognito mode , simply close the window with incognito enabled .
#Text=In Firefox , you can press ++ .
#Text=To exit this window in Firefox , press the same buttons .
#Text=In Google Chrome , you can press ++ to enter Incognito Mode .
#Text=To exit incognito mode , simply close the window with incognito enabled .
#Text=Alternate Browser Method
#Text=Download another internet browser such as Firefox or Safari .
#Text=Do not make this browser your default browser .
#Text=When you install it make sure to not set as your default browser .
#Text=Clear all evidence of the installation .
#Text=If you are using Windows , delete the quick launch shortcut and move it to some safe location .
#Text=Use this browser to surf the internet privately .
#Text=Now , you can use the other browser for stuff you do n't want your parents to know about .
#Text=The favourites , history , cache , and cookies will be separate from your normal browser .
#Text=Your parents will continue to use the other browser normally , and even if they check the history they wo n't find anything , but make sure they do n't notice the other browser .
#Text=Portable Firefox Method
#Text=Select a device to host your portable applications .
#Text=Any cell phone , MP3 player , camera , USB flash drive , or portable hard drive which comes up as a removable device in Windows will work .
#Text=Download the Portable Firefox .
#Text=You can search it on Google .
#Text=Install their launcher menu and then portable Firefox on your device .
#Text=Restart your device .
#Text=You can do this by unplugging your device and plunging it back in , or you can turn it off , then turn it back on .
#Text=Unblock Windows Firewall .
#Text=Windows will ask you what you want to do ; let it start PortableAppz.blogspot.com ; this will open the menu .
#Text=Red , looks like the Start menu , comes up on the right .
#Text=Click the Firefox icon/name on the menu .
#Text=Portable Firefox will keep all of your bookmarks , history , and settings on your device ; it wo n't leave anything behind on the host computer .
#Text=You can take it to a friend 's house , hook it up , and all of your stuff is there .
#Text=4GB and 8GB flash drives can be bought for very cheap now online and in some stores .
#Text=Corsair drives tend to have the fastest speeds .
#Text=Be sure to exit the menu ( grey circle with white arrow ) when you 're done using it .
#Text=VPN
#Text=For a VPN is the newer way to hide data online , the Incognito tab , cannot hide data from your router , but a VPN such as Tor can .
#Text=They are also connected to the dark web sites , so are made to be anonymous .
#Text=Tips
#Text=It 's best to be alone when searching something you do n't want your parents seeing .
#Text=Use your instinct - it 's better to be safe than sorry when it comes to things like this .
#Text=On Internet Explorer , delete your history by clicking tools , then click " delete browsing history " and click delete all .
#Text=On Firefox , click tools , then click " clear private data " and click " clear private data " now .
#Text=A Windows 7 is the best computer for this because the internet tabs do not show a preview of the description of websites .
#Text=If there is one in your house , use it .

#Text=If you 're technically minded , then you can use a proxy website which will retrieve the packet data from another server , not your internet service provider , this will hide it from any parent controls installed on the router or family safety program .
#Text=You could also use a Free VPN service which will divert all internet logs to another server .
#Text=Do n't use Google , use DuckDuckGo instead , because Google keeps a log of what you searched for that you ca n't erase , but DuckDuckGo does not .
#Text=Warnings
#Text=If your parents find out , you may lose computer privileges or have parental controls turned on and block the sites they do n't want you on .
#Text=Your parents do everything for your own good .
#Text=It is better to obey them and not to disobey .
#Text=They are much more experienced and probably wo n't allow anything which could harm their children .
